zimwriterfs
------------------------------------------
zimwriterfs is a console tool to create ZIM files from a locally-stored
directory containing 'self-sufficient' HTML content (with pictures, javascript
and stylesheets). The result will contain all the files of the local directory
compressed and merged in the ZIM file. Nothing more, nothing less. The
generated file can be opened with a ZIM reader; Kiwix is one example, but there
are others.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  file-5.32-1
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libgumbo1-0.10.1-1bl1
  libicu65-65.1-1
  libstdc++6-7.4.0-1
  libzim6-6.0.2-1bl1
  zlib0-1.2.11-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  meson-0.51.2-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/openzim/zimwriterfs

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/openzim/zimwriterfs/archive/1.3.7.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack zimwriterfs-1.3.7-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./zimwriterfs-1.3.7-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/zimwriterfs-1.3.7-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/zimwriterfs-1.3.7-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(zimwriterfs)
  /usr/bin/zimwriterfs.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/zimwriterfs.README
  /usr/share/doc/zimwriterfs/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/zimwriterfs/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/zimwriterfs/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/zimwriterfs/README.md

